Recommends: acl
Description: Linux-first voice-to-text dictation tool
 whisrs is a voice dictation system for Linux desktops and compositors.
 Press a hotkey, speak, and transcribed text is typed at the cursor.
 .
 This package installs the whisrs CLI client, the whisrsd background
 daemon, a systemd user unit, and a udev rule for /dev/uinput access.
 Cloud backends (Groq, Deepgram, OpenAI) and offline whisper.cpp are
 included in the default build.
